Storm: Stand. That is enough.

You’re using intimidation where clarity would work. Or you’re shrinking because you forgot your size.

One decisive move.

Storm: Hold the line. No exceptions.

You’re over-controlling because you don’t trust life. Or you’re reckless because you’re numb.

Act instantly.

Attention is power when it is clean.

Oct watches the trace before it becomes story. It offers presence, not command.

Insight.

advice: Truth arrives fast. The window is short. Act cleanly and decisively.
Treat this as guidance, not a fixed outcome.
